==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: icebreaker
<hw>icebreaker</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a ship with a
reinforced bow and powerful engines designed to break up layers of ice
on waterways and keep channels open for navigation.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> iceboat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A remark or action intended to relieve tension or
reduce formality when initiating conversation or beginning a speech; it
is often a humorous or light remark.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ice-built</ent>⟦br⟧
